  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Bash your<strong> lemongrass</strong> with a<strong> rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> and set aside for later, then chop the <strong>softer inner core[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/basa-tom-kha-soup-with-lemongrass-rice/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>,<strong> outer lemongrass layers</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/basa-tom-kha-soup-with-lemongrass-rice/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely, then chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/basa-tom-kha-soup-with-lemongrass-rice/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>in 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped lemongrass</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/basa-tom-kha-soup-with-lemongrass-rice/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly thickened</p><p>Once thickened, add the<strong> chopped basa </strong>and cook, covered, for 4-5 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/basa-tom-kha-soup-with-lemongrass-rice/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, pick your<strong> coriander leaves</strong> from their stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander stalks</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/basa-tom-kha-soup-with-lemongrass-rice/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is cooked through, add the<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lime[s]</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good stir – this is your <strong>basa tom kha soup</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Discard the<strong> outer lemongrass layers</strong> from the <strong>lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/basa-tom-kha-soup-with-lemongrass-rice/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>basa tom kha soup</strong> in a bowl with the<strong> lemongrass rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>coriander leaves</strong>, <strong>chopped coriander stalks</strong> and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
